Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
add_gui_text(25.10)                                        add_gui_text(25.10)

Name
       add_gui_text

Syntax
       add_gui_text

       [-help]

       [-alignment  {upperLeft  centerLeft  lowerLeft upperCenter centerCenter
       lowerCenter upperRight centerRight lowerRight}]

       -label <text>

       -layer <layerName>

       {-box {<x1 y1 x2 y2>} | {{-height <height> | -fixed_height <fixHeight>}
       -pt {<x y>}  [-orient <direction>]}}

       [-box {<x1 y1 x2 y2>} [-no_bbox]]

       Adds text (annotation) to the specified custom layer. You can  use  the
       add_gui_text command at any point in the design flow. The text added by
       the  command  annotates comment text and does not show up in a DEF out-
       put.

       Note: In OpenAccess flows, any text added with the add_gui_text command
       is stored in the OpenAccess cellview. However, the text is stored in  a
       private  structure  that  is accessible only to Innovus. To create text
       that is visible in Virtuoso as well, use the add_text command instead.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each add_gui_text parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man add_gui_text

       -alignment {upperLeft centerLeft lowerLeft upperCenter centerCenter
       lowerCenter upperRight centerRight lowerRight}
              Specifies the alignment of the text. The setting you specify  is
              saved in the database and can be streamed out into a GDSII file.
              When  the GDSII file is loaded into a K2 viewer or streamed into
              Virtuoso, the added text is displayed as per the alignment  set-
              ting.

              The  -alignment  setting does not impact the text display within
              Innovus.

       -box {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies the coordinates of the rectangle in which text will be
              added. The coordinate values are specified in microns. When this
              parameter is used, the tool figures out  the  correct  size  and
              orientation to be used to fit the text into the box. The text is
              center justified in the box.

              Use this parameter to control the text orientation and size.

       -height <height>
              Specifies the height of the text in microns.

       -fixed_height <fixHeight>
              Specifies the height in pixels. <fixHeight> should be an integer
              value.

       -label <text>
              Specifies the text to be displayed. If your text has spaces, en-
              close it in quotation marks or braces.

       -layer <layerName>
              Specifies  the GUI layer name to use or create for the text.  If
              the specified layer does not exist,  it  will  be  automatically
              created.

       -no_bbox
              Specifies  that  bounding  box  should not be drawn when text is
              displayed at the specified box coordinates. This  parameter  can
              be used only when -box is specified.

       -orient <direction>
              Specifies the orientation of the text. Possible values are:

               MX MX90 MY MY90 R0 R90 R180 R270

              This option cannot be used with -box.

       -pt {<x y>}
              Specifies the origin coordinate of the text (microns).

Examples
              * The  following command adds the text label Sample Text Display
                with size of 18 pixels on layer 1 at the specified point coor-
                dinates:

                add_gui_text   -layer   1   -label   "Sample   Text   Display"
                -fixed_height 18 -pt {0 250}

              * The  following command adds the text label Sample Text Display
                on layer 1 in a box with the  specified  coordinates.  As  the
                length  of  the  box  is more than the width, the text is dis-
                played horizontally:

                add_gui_text -layer 1 -box {0 250 500 450} -label "Sample Text
                Display"

              * The following command adds the text label Sample Text  Display
                on  layer  1  in  a box with the specified coordinates. As the
                height of the box is more than the width,  the  text  is  dis-
                played vertically:

                add_gui_text -layer 1 -box {0 250 200 750} -label "Sample Text
                Display"

              * The  following command adds the text label Sample Text Display
                on layer 1 at the  specified  box  coordinates.  However,  the
                bounding box is not displayed:

                add_gui_text  -layer  1  -box  {0 250 500 450} -no_bbox -label
                "Sample Text Display"

